tml,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "format": "dash-1293270476006520v - 720x1280 (DASH video)"}, {"format_id": "dash-2077012489752055v", "ext": "mp4", "width": 1080, "height": 1920, "tbr": 1473.633, "format_note": "DASH video", "container": "mp4_dash", "vcodec": "vp09.00.40.08.00.01.01.01.00", "acodec": "none", "dynamic_range": "SDR", "url": "https://scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com/o1/v/t2/f2/m367/AQOOpP7SSbW6qIE8K_MAXZAWIWfIn_Cwi_dyzTeN3ntgweCtNciI9A64IqxcidII3VWiWprMh5mFVkxjihBVhNXxUa0QEdCn_XVoxAAwLjLK_Q.mp4?_nc_cat=102&_nc_sid=9ca052&_nc_ht=scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_ohc=9GmwgnxSP_gQ7kNvwEurrl0&&ccb=17-1&_nc_gid=xkFO0ghL0u0zgy7wdlBOJQ&_nc_zt=28&_nc_ss=7a32e&oh=00_Af1Lz4-llBVPbRvFQrcfc_s8ppEn_EhjueKxhM1uwplDDw&oe=69D4C416", "manifest_stream_number": 0, "is_dash_periods": true, "protocol": "https", "video_ext": "mp4", "audio_ext": "none", "abr": 0, "vbr": 1473.633, "resolution": "1080x1920", "aspect_ratio": 0.56, "filesize_approx": 20372976, "http_headers": {"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/143.0.0.0 Safari/537.36", "Accept": "text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "format": "dash-2077012489752055v - 1080x1920 (DASH video)"}], "title": "Video by brandonsbrainwave", "description": "I love breathwork \n\nBreathing is something we all do everyday, but most people actually do it incorrectly \n\nTraining your breathing in this way with breath holds can improve your CO2 tolerance and retrain your nervous system to regulate your breathing more effectively 💨 \n\nMost people breathe too quickly, which keeps them in fight or flight, but doing breath holds can teach your body to breathe more slowly and calmly \n\nLet me know if this helps ✌️ \nFollow for more 👇 \n\n#neuroscience #spirituality #breathe #fitness #health", "duration": 110.6, "timestamp": 1773258408, "uploader_id": "8411219198", "uploader": "Brandon Cowling", "channel": "brandonsbrainwave", "like_count": 944, "comment_count": 23, "comments": [{"author": "alexleftchat", "author_id": "5710919589", "id": "17930991774237355", "text": "I almost passed out trying it before i got to the warning 😭", "timestamp": 1773357206}, {"author": "inzom_ox", "author_id": "54281846", "id": "18096454561804325", "text": "", "timestamp": 1773346355}, {"author": "matthiashaertwig", "author_id": "7349665099", "id": "18060835166690858", "text": "how about usind the word \"sane\" instead of \"insane\"? I know it is a common saying, just don't resonate with it's vibration or meaning. And I think you can surely replace that with something you like aswell and find joy in. Since you are so interested in all of that, I thought I might share. Greetings and Blessings brother, thanks for your great work! :)", "timestamp": 1773303296}, {"author": "whoisthiswilliam", "author_id": "274437301", "id": "18043507763737437", "text": "Hey bro so I shouldnt be worried when I meditate and stop breathing during the meditation practice? Better to “hold breath” than to “fake breathe” right? When Im too focus, I use to forget breathing and I feel awkward", "timestamp": 1773295214}, {"author": "victercovarrubias", "author_id": "32290450088", "id": "17951384061066938", "text": "Love your videos, is that Ocushield you’re wearing?", "timestamp": 1773294790}], "thumbnails": [{"url": "https://scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.71878-15/649241966_2698611843843659_4527519277754622607_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6ImltYWdlX3VybGdlbi42NDB4MTEzNi5zZHIuZjcxODc4LmRlZmF1bHRfY292ZXJfZnJhbWUuYzIifQ&_nc_ht=scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=111&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gGco2g9H9J93nAvWlisYqjjEbVDDXuK-9D-GwdgobWhLdycA8Zk9hFTUNmnBQO8pCA&_nc_ohc=XfDv-lEyPOsQ7kNvwHlMfvd&_nc_gid=xkFO0